<subSubSection lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="35.[264,1324,1677,1904]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,439,1757,1783]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[456,716,1758,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Seeversiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis box="[456,716,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Seeversiella nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Seeversiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Seeversiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having brown body; temples twice as long as eyes; glossy pronotum with weak and partially missing microsculpture; elytra longer than pronotum; wings fully developed; tergum 
<number box="[353,368,1878,1904]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="8.0">8</number>
with four pairs of macrosetae; and the distinct shape of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1311,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURES 117 ­ 125" captionStartId="36.[264,383,1644,1668]" captionTargetBox="[297,1299,423,1607]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[279,1307,409,1617]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 117 ­ 125. Abdominal segment 8 and aedeagus of Seeversiella nigriceps Gusarov, sp. n. (holotype). 117 – male tergum 8; 118 – male sternum 8; 119 – median lobe, parameral view; 120 – apex of median lobe, parameral view; 121 – median lobe, lateral view; 122 – apex of median lobe, lateral view; 123 ­ 124 – details of internal sac retracted into median lobe, lateral view; 125 – apex of left paramere. Scale bar 0.3 mm (117 ­ 118), 0.2 mm (119, 121, 123 ­ 124), 0.1 mm (120, 122, 125). DS – distal sclerite of internal sac." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156441/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Figs. 
<number box="[1209,1311,1878,1904]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="122.0" valueMax="125.0" valueMin="119.0">119­125</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1323,284,350]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName box="[312,570,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Seeversiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis box="[312,570,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Seeversiella nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from closely related 
<taxonomicName box="[902,1093,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Seeversiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sonomotoides">
<emphasis box="[902,1093,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">S. sonomotoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having narrower distal sclerites of internal sac of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[767,880,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURES 117 ­ 125" captionStartId="36.[264,383,1644,1668]" captionTargetBox="[297,1299,423,1607]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[279,1307,409,1617]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 117 ­ 125. Abdominal segment 8 and aedeagus of Seeversiella nigriceps Gusarov, sp. n. (holotype). 117 – male tergum 8; 118 – male sternum 8; 119 – median lobe, parameral view; 120 – apex of median lobe, parameral view; 121 – median lobe, lateral view; 122 – apex of median lobe, lateral view; 123 ­ 124 – details of internal sac retracted into median lobe, lateral view; 125 – apex of left paramere. Scale bar 0.3 mm (117 ­ 118), 0.2 mm (119, 121, 123 ­ 124), 0.1 mm (120, 122, 125). DS – distal sclerite of internal sac." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156441/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Figs. 
<number box="[833,880,324,350]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="124.0">124</number>
</figureCitation>
; 63, 65).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156441/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" targetBox="[297,1299,423,1607]" targetPageId="36">
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1322,1644,1840]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,477,1644,1668]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">FIGURES 117­125</emphasis>
. Abdominal segment 8 and aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gusarov" authorityName="Gusarov" box="[919,1251,1644,1667]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Seeversiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[919,1153,1644,1667]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Seeversiella nigriceps</emphasis>
Gusarov
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1263,1322,1644,1668]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1263,1322,1644,1668]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(holotype). 117 – male tergum 8; 118 – male sternum 8; 119 – median lobe, parameral view; 120 – apex of median lobe, parameral view; 121 – median lobe, lateral view; 122 – apex of median lobe, lateral view; 123­124 – details of internal sac retracted into median lobe, lateral view; 125 – apex of left paramere. Scale bar 0.3 mm (117­118), 0.2 mm (119, 121, 123­124), 0.1 mm (120, 122, 125). DS – distal sclerite of internal sac.
</paragraph>
