<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,472,763,789]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from 
<collectingCountry box="[645,735,764,790]" name="Mexico" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[750,853,764,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="97.[264,368,1861,1885]" captionTargetBox="[313,1275,771,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@97.[304,1282,766,1834]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="FIGURE 387. Geographical distribution of Seeversiella from Mexico to Honduras." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156489/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Fig. 
<number box="[805,853,764,790]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" value="387.0">387</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[264,1324,284,870]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,516,803,829]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Natural History.</emphasis>
The only known specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[876,1014,804,829]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Seeversiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis box="[876,1014,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">S. nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in forest litter at altitude of 
<quantity box="[458,549,844,870]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.41" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="m" value="2410.0">2410 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
